    <h4>Hosting</h4>
    <p>
        - 'Hosting' is where you store content (usually files, websites, etc.) on servers.<br>
        - These servers need to have very high uptime, and often need lots of bandwidth, so most
        hosting happens with third parties who have the expertise and infrastructure to achieve this.<br>
        - It is quite rare to find a website hosted entirely on the infrastructure of the organisation
        behind it without using any third-party hosting.<br>
        - Servers must also have protection from attacks like (DDoS or Distributed Denial of Service) attacks
        which overload a server and cause the application to become unusable for actual users.<br>
        - The IP address of the server must remain the same, or the server must use a DDNS (Dynamic DNS) service
        to make sure it is accessible at any time, and you don't have to go updating DNS records
        every time your IP address changes.
    </p>
